\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b 3) if-else-if ladder:\cf0\b0\par
The if-else-if statement contains the if-statement followed by multiple else-if statements. \par
\b Example 1:\b0\par

\pard\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf1 import java.util.Scanner;\par
public class Main \{\par
    public static void main(String[] args) \{\par
        Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);\par
        System.out.print("Enter your marks (0-100): ");\par
        int marks = scanner.nextInt();\par
        // if-else-if ladder\par
        if (marks >= 90) \{\par
            System.out.println("Grade: A+");\par
        \} else if (marks >= 80) \{\par
            System.out.println("Grade: A");\par
        \} else if (marks >= 70) \{\par
            System.out.println("Grade: B");\par
        \} else if (marks >= 60) \{\par
            System.out.println("Grade: C");\par
        \} else if (marks >= 50) \{\par
            System.out.println("Grade: D");\par
        \} else \{\par
            System.out.println("Grade: F (Fail)");\par
        \}\par
    \}\par
\}\par

