\b Loop statements:\b0\par
A loop lets you repeat a block of code multiple times, automatically.\par
Instead of writing the same line of code over and over, you use a loop to do it for you.\par
There are 3 main types of loops in Java:\par

\pard\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1 1. for loop\par
2. while loop\par
3. do while loop\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf1\b 1. for loop \f2\endash  \cf0\b0\par
when you know how many times to repeat\par
\b\f0\lang16393 Example 1:\b0\par

\pard\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf1 for (int i = 1; i <= 5; i++) \{\par
    System.out.println("Hello " + i);\par
\}\par

